{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1775568026,"nonce":"ZeXW8x4+hOTXiMXF6tUfnEt0808=","title":"docs: update Datenschutzerklärung with cookie information","message":"The privacy policy (Datenschutzerklärung) needs to document which cookies\nthe application sets, their purpose, and retention.\n\nBonanza uses only strictly necessary cookies (no consent banner needed):\n\n- _bonanza_session: Rails session cookie (login/auth)\n- department: remembers current department selection\n- Devise remember-me cookie (if enabled)\n\nThese are functional cookies exempt from consent under ePrivacy/GDPR.\nHowever, they must be documented in the privacy policy.\n\nUpdate the Datenschutzerklärung in the legal_texts table (or the template\nat /datenschutz) to include a section on cookies.\n\nP2 — documentation requirement, not blocking functionality.","files":null}]}